      .section#story.foo2
        .title.is-2: b Story
        .subtitle.is-4 A little flavor to the event
        hr
        .columns
          .column(style="text-align:right !important")
            img(src="/images/vertical-sfk.png" )
          .column.is-5
            br
            .title Solstice
            .subtitle Two sides of the same earth
            .quote
                p.
                    As the solstice approaches, 
                p.
                    north and south will meet two very distinct pictures-
                br

                p.
                    The bright and cheerful afternoons 
                p.
                    towards the end of the sunny month of June,
                p.
                    when the north wind congregates in crowds
                p.
                    the floating mountains of the silver clouds from the horizon,
                p.
                    and the stainless sky opens beyond them like eternity. 
                p.
                    All things rejoiced beneath the sun;
                p.
                    the weeds, the river, and the willow 
                p.
                    leaves that glanced in the light breeze.
                br

                p.
                    And the never ending nights of a winter 
                p.
                    such as when birds die in the deep forests; 
                p.
                    and the fishes lie stiffened in the translucent ice, 
                p.
                    which makes even the mud and slime of the warm lakes 
                p.
                    a wrinkled clod as hard as brick.
                p.
                    Among their children, comfortable men 
                p.
                    gather about great fires, 
                p.
                    and yet feel cold.
                br

                p.
                    Praising their own deities 
                p.
                    in tribute of these sceneries, 
                p.
                    are the Ice Queen and the Fey druidess, 
                p.
                    both leading their fellows 
                p.
                    to prove themselves the more devoted 
                p.
                    in name of the winter and the summer spirits.
            hr
            .div
                p.
                    In this event you will join in either of these factions, and follow the path of strife to prove yourselves the most devoted. But choose wisely, once you've contracted a bond with one of them, it cannot be undone.
                br
                p.
                    As a member of one of these factions, you will need to collect tributes to your respective priestess.
                br
                p
                    span.
                        To <b>Nikoliny, the Ice Queen</b>. You should collect <b>Crystalline Snowflakes</b>.
                    br
                    span.
                        And to <b>Cecily, the Fey Druidess</b>. You should collect <b>Blossoming Flowers</b>.

      
      .section#cast.foo2
        .title.is-2: b Meet the mascots    
        .subtitle.is-4 Who's joining us this month for the event
        hr
            
        .columns.is-mobile
          .column(style="text-align:right !important")

            .foo
              img(src="/images/nkmug.png" style="max-height:86vh" )
            .foo
              hr
              .title Cecily
              .subtitle The Fey Druidess
              p: i Legends tell about this wanderer of the wild. The druidess that can connect with nature itself, and every deity that seeks seclusion within the woods. Cecily inhabits the craddle of Shaedyn civilization, the Liizhaea continent, within the untouched depths of its ever green forest heart. Every year Cecily provides a few treats as a tribute to the deities.
                br
                | Your quest as a supporter of the Summer Team is to help the Fey Druidess gather the Blossoming Flowers to be offered as tribute to the gods. Cecy will reward you for your kindness.
              br
              p Cosmetics listing

          .column
            
            .foo(style="margin-top:100px")
              hr
              .title#niky Nikoliny
              .subtitle The Ice Queen
              p: i The legendary Queen from the forgotten southen plains of Nanuk, South Amarok. The shining bride of the gods, who reigns over everything the ice touches, as long as she can satisfy the deities with enough tributes.
                br
                | Your quest as a supporter of the Winter Team is to help the Ice Queen to gather the Crystaline Snowflakes demanded as tribute for the gods. Niky will reward you for your kindness.
              br
              p Cosmetics listing
            br#cecy
            br
            .foo
              img(src="/images/ccmug.png" style="max-height:86vh" )
              
        .title#australis And there's a returning guest this time!      
        .columns
          .column(style="text-align:right !important")
            .foo
              img(src="/images/austramug.png" style="max-height:86vh" )
          .column            
            .foo(style="margin-top:100px")
              hr
              .title Australis
              .subtitle The Elf Trader (From December 2017 PolluXmas Event)
              p: i Australis is the elf of Midsummer Xmas, at Santa's southern assembly lines. Always greedy and always looking for some way to get as much Rubines as possible on her way.
              br
              p Australis trades Flowers and Snowflakes for Rubines, she can tamper with your Server's lootbox drop rate depending on how much you put in her hands.
            br
            
      hr
